text: Resolis (from the Scottish Gaelic Ruigh Sholais meaning Bright Slope) is a village and parish on the B9163 road, in the Black Isle in Scotland. It is part of the Presbytery of Ross. In 2011 it had a population of 362. ==Notable People== *Rev Hector Cameron born and raised here. == References == Category:Villages in Highland (council area) Category:Black Isle Category:Parishes of Scotland
title: Resolis
